SIMPLE: stumpage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stumpage
<hw>Stump"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Timber
in standing trees, -- often sold without the land at a fixed price per
tree or per stump, the stumps being counted when the land is
cleared.</def> <mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Only trees above a certain size are allowed to be cut by loggers
buying <qex>stumpage</qex> from the owners of land.</q> <rj><qau>C. S.
Sargent.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tax on the amount of timber cut, regulated by the
price of lumber.</def> <mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark> <rj><au>The
Nation.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stumper</ent>⟦br⟧
